        <h2 id="pricing-breakdown">Pricing Breakdown: The Real Numbers</h2>

        <p>Forget the "starting at" marketing nonsense. Here's what you'll actually pay based on real customer data from 2026:</p>

        <h3>Housecall Pro Pricing</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>3 users:</strong> $79/month ($948/year)</li>
          <li><strong>5 users:</strong> $149/month ($1,788/year)</li>
          <li><strong>10 users:</strong> $299/month ($3,588/year)</li>
          <li><strong>15 users:</strong> $449/month ($5,388/year)</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Add $50/month for advanced reporting, $30/month for inventory management. Payment processing costs 2.9% + $0.30 per transaction.</p>

        <h3>ServiceTitan Pricing</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>5 users:</strong> $300-400/month ($3,600-4,800/year)</li>
          <li><strong>10 users:</strong> $600-800/month ($7,200-9,600/year)</li>
          <li><strong>20 users:</strong> $1,200-1,600/month ($14,400-19,200/year)</li>
          <li><strong>50+ users:</strong> $2,500-4,000+/month (custom pricing)</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Includes most features in base price. Payment processing costs 2.8% + $0.25 per transaction. Annual contracts mandatory with 20% discount.</p>

        <h3>Jobber Pricing</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>3 users:</strong> $129/month ($1,548/year)</li>
          <li><strong>5 users:</strong> $199/month ($2,388/year)</li>
          <li><strong>10 users:</strong> $349/month ($4,188/year)</li>
          <li><strong>20 users:</strong> $599/month ($7,188/year)</li>
        </ul>

        <p>QuickBooks integration costs extra $29/month. Payment processing ranges from 2.9% to 3.5% depending on volume.</p>

        <div style="background: #e8f4f8; padding: 1.5rem; border-left: 4px solid #1B4F72; margin: 2rem 0;">
          <p style="margin: 0; font-weight: 600;">ROI Reality Check:</p>
          <p style="margin: 0.5rem 0 0;">A 10-person HVAC team typically sees 15-25% revenue increase in year one from better scheduling and follow-up automation. That's $75,000-125,000 extra revenue on a $500,000 business, easily justifying any of these CRM investments.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="team-size-fit">Team Size & Growth Fit</h2>

        <h3>1-5 Person Teams: Housecall Pro Wins</h3>
        <p>For small residential HVAC companies, Housecall Pro delivers 90% of what you need at half the cost. The interface is simple enough that your wife can handle dispatching without training. Customer texting, basic scheduling, and payment processing work flawlessly.</p>

        <p><strong>Growth ceiling:</strong> Starts showing cracks around 12-15 technicians when you need advanced reporting and multi-location management.</p>

        <div style="text-align: center; margin: 2rem 0;">
          <a href="https://housecallpro.partnerlinks.io/auy5xcz257sw" rel="sponsored nofollow" style="display: inline-block; background: #007acc; color: white; padding: 12px 24px; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 5px; font-weight: 600;">Try Housecall Pro Free →</a>
        </div>

        <h3>3-25 Person Teams: Jobber Takes the Crown</h3>
        <p>Jobber hits the sweet spot for growing HVAC companies. The automation features save 3-5 hours per week on follow-ups and scheduling. Mobile app gets technicians productive faster than competitors.</p>

        <p>Real example: Thompson HVAC in Phoenix grew from 8 to 22 technicians on Jobber without switching platforms. Their average ticket increased 18% from better upselling prompts in the mobile app.</p>

        <div style="text-align: center; margin: 2rem 0;">
          <a href="https://go.getjobber.com/bo42cjptz4m2" rel="sponsored nofollow" style="display: inline-block; background: #28a745; color: white; padding: 12px 24px; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 5px; font-weight: 600;">Start Jobber Free Trial →</a>
        </div>

        <h3>15+ Person Teams: ServiceTitan Dominates</h3>
        <p>Once you hit 15+ technicians, ServiceTitan's complexity becomes an asset. Advanced reporting shows which technicians are underperforming, which service areas generate highest profits, and which marketing channels deliver best customers.</p>

        <p>Commercial HVAC companies especially benefit from project management features and multi-location billing capabilities that smaller CRMs can't match.</p>

